history.content:
You didn't give any information about your major or class standing, so we can't give advice based on http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml 

Assuming you have priority to enroll in both, you should phase 1 whichever of the two courses you have least flexibility in terms of discussion and lab times as it is likely (although not certain) that we will be able to expand both to meet demand.

61B and 70 are both a lot of work but are also often taken together and taking them with two non-technical courses is a good way to plan vis a vis workload. You may consider taking your AC course P/NP if possible.
